{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6bb99b4d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1281a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1281a"},"text":"§ 1281a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Total treatment system funding","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, in any case where the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency finds that the total of all grants made under section 201 of the Federal Water Pollution Control Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1281"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 1281","children":[],"tail":"] for the same treatment works exceeds the actual construction costs for such treatment works (as defined in that Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1251"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 1251","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]) such excess amount shall be a grant of the Federal share (as defined in that Act) of the cost of construction of a sewage collection system if—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6bb99b4e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1281a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such sewage collection system was constructed as part of the same total treatment system as the treatment works for which such section 201 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1281"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 1281","children":[],"tail":"] grants were approved, and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id6bb99b4f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1281a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an application for assistance for the construction of such sewage collection system was filed in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3102"},"text":"section 3102 of title 42","children":[],"tail":" before all such section 201 grants were made and such grant under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3102"},"text":"section 3102 of title 42","children":[],"tail":" could not be approved due to lack of funding under such "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3102"},"text":"section 3102 of title 42","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"The total of all grants for sewage collection systems made under this section shall not exceed $2,800,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6bb99b50-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217/s78"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217, § 78","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1611"},"text":"91 Stat. 1611","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6bb99b51-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6bb99b52-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6bb99b53-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"That Act, meaning the Federal Water Pollution Control Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-30/ch758"},"text":"act June 30, 1948, ch. 758","children":[],"tail":", as amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/500/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–500, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/816"},"text":"86 Stat. 816","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1251"},"text":"section 1251 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3102"},"text":"Section 3102 of title 42","children":[],"tail":", referred to in par. (2), was omitted from the Code pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5316"},"text":"section 5316 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, which terminated the authority to make grants or loans under that section after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6bb99b54-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Clean Water Act of 1977, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217","children":[],"tail":", and not as part of the Federal Water Pollution Control Act which comprises this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
